# Gear Restrictions {#gear-restrictions}

## General Guidance {#general-guidance}

* Members are to suit their [weapons](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/12d9Oeodl1lcEx018_ogCIaJaQr7nMiaAWBVr4nUD6ZI/edit?usp=sharing) to their role unless the mission specifies them otherwise.  
  * If unsure, query with the SL/PL  
* Only gear that is available in the arsenal is to be used on standard operations unless this has been predesignated by the mission maker.  
* Battalion uniform applies to ALL MEMBERS unless the mission maker has predesignated this.  
* SL, FL, RTO use Laser Designators.  
* Long Range Radios to be carried by SL, FL, RTO.  
* No Thermal NVG’s.  
* No Thermal Weapon Scopes.  
* Rugged Tablet only for FS, PLs, SLs and Support.  
* Helmets are recommended but not mandatory.  
* Enemy weapons are only allowed to take if you run out of ammo and are unable to rearm from your squad.

### Weapon Specifics {#weapon-specifics}

* Suppressors can be used within a Squad's Fireteam to suit its play style. SL/PL can negate the use of suppressors if they think it is not needed for the Squad.  
* The Squad Marksman may use a Bolt Action Rifle if they have the badge and if the SL approves.  
* A maximum of 4x scopes for all Members, except for Marksman and Snipers.  
* High capacity magazines only for MG gunners  
  * 50 round mags or more  
* 50cal and M32 Grenade launcher is only to be used after FS approval.

## Roles/Slots {#roles/slots}

Members must adhere to the role they select upon entering the mission and, by proxy, bring the gear associated with that role. Guests or staff such as “Division Commander”, “Head Drill Instructor”, etc. must fill a role given to them by the squad leader that they are joining unless they are fulfilling a specific task with their presence.

Running multiple roles at once is not allowed, RTO is excluded from this rule. However, if a squad is very low on numbers then it is up to the squad leader's discretion to allow multi roles to cover the basics, such as Medic and AT.

### Platoon Leaders {#platoon-leaders}

* Laser Designators to be used in this role  
* Long Range Radios need to be carried  
* AR Darter Drones can be used  
* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry  
* Can have disposables launchers(1 SHOT) only

### Squad Leaders/Fireteam Leaders {#squad-leaders/fireteam-leaders}

* Laser Designators to be used in this role  
* Long Range Radios need to be carried  
* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry  
* Can have disposables launchers(1 SHOT) only

### Infantry Roles:  {#infantry-roles:}

#### Rifleman: {#rifleman:}

* Can carry ammo/equipment for other roles, e.g. Medicals supplies  
* Can have disposables launchers(1 SHOT) only  
* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry

#### Machine gunner: {#machine-gunner:}

* A high capacity magazine can be used  
* To use LMG/HMG type of weaponry

#### AT/AA: {#at/aa:}

* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry  
* Can carry reusable launchers 

#### Medic: {#medic:}

* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry.  
* Need to carry stitching Kit and defibrillation unit  
* Carry a good amount of medical supplies (Not overbearing)

#### Engineer/EOD: {#engineer/eod:}

* Only to use Rifle type of weaponry  
* Explosives can be carried  
* Need to carry explosive detonator, toolkit and Mine detector

#### Marksman/Sniper {#marksman/sniper}

* DMR or Sniper rifles type of weaponry can be used  
* Can use scopes higher than 4x

##### Marksman Only {#marksman-only}

* MK 11 (all variants)  
* Scar-H/Mk 17 (long barrel)  
* M14 EBR-RI (RHS)  
* GX Guns  
* M14 (classic)  
* Scar-H (standard barrel)  
* QBU-88  
* MSBS Grot MR  
* VS-121  
* SVDM  
* SVDS  
* MXM

##### DMRs but free to use as a Rifle {#dmrs-but-free-to-use-as-a-rifle}

* M14 (all RHS variants)  
* IMI Galil ARM 308  
* HK417  
* SMI G3/CETME  
* HCAR  
* SIG 556  
* Mk14 EBR (vanilla)  
* M14 (vanilla)

#### Support: {#support:}

* Carry Medical Equipment to assist other squads, where applicable.  
* Carry Engineering Equipment to repair assets.  
* Only carry Assault Rifles/SMGs/Pistols.  
* Long Range Radios are to be used by all members of support.  
* Correct uniform and headgear should be used depending on the support member's role to align with the task they are completing. (eg. flying \= flight suit), (ground crew \= infantry uniform \-with relevant headgear)

# Standard Procedures {#standard-procedures}

## Members {#members}

* Every and all complaints, requests, ideas, etc. go through our battalion form. Before that, they are not official and actions won’t be taken upon them, unless BATCOM sees an urgent need.  
* If members have an issue with a mission, they put in their own feedback through the battalion form. Feedback given per voice or in some channels can’t be taken into account.

## Overall Leadership {#overall-leadership}

* Rules (Section 7, etc.), gear restrictions and badge requirements are enforced by every Staff member (everyone in a position) at all times. If any staff member notices anything, they will bring it up to the COC of the member.  
* SLs are responsible to speak for their members. Field changes will be discussed on NCO level or higher and battalion votes only occur in special cases.  
* Every document used is in the battalion Google Drive folder of the involved office, and its owner has been changed to [amdivision.taw@gmail.com](mailto:amdivision.taw@gmail.com).  
* All documents are frequently checked and old files are getting archived.  
* TS channels (including files) and Discord Pins are kept up to date.  
* Squad Leaders to check TeamSpeak channels are updated every 1st of month.

## FS and Field Leadership {#fs-and-field-leadership}

* Overall mission planning is done before the NCO meeting in the mission-planning channel by the FS, so PLs have time to make their plan. At the NCO meeting that plan will be discussed with the FS and approved. Afterwards the plan will be forwarded to the SLs.  
* The overall battle plan is marked out on the CP for everyone to see.  
* During battalion missions, 1st and 2nd Platoon should be split up between objectives, with some distance between them, to improve FPS and avoid rubber banding.  
* Monthly FL meetings are in place to talk about consistent issues and things that need to be improved.  
* After a bad mission or a mission with many issues (except Server issues), a meeting is held with all required Field Leaders, Zeuses and the mission maker to figure out what went wrong and how to improve in the future.  
* Every SL puts in their squad feedback after every battalion event.  
* When the SL is unable to attend an event, an available FL should take over. If no FL is available, another capable squad member or an AL should take over. If that is also not possible, a PL can step in if available.

## Ingame {#ingame}

* Badge Requirements and gear restrictions are followed by every member as well as enforced by every staff member.  
* Line up is at 0725 pm and the battalion is ready to move out at 0730 pm. SLs and PLs are responsible for this.  
* Line up are proper lines.

![][image1]

* The correct camo type is used for Helmet, Vest, Backpack and Uniform.  
  ***Available camo:***	  
  Alpine (Snowy Terrians)  
  AOR1 (Arid/Desert Terrians)  
  Multicam (Variety, Most urban Terrians)  
  Multicam Tropic (Lush Forest, Jungle Terrians)  
  Multicam Black (Night Ops)

* War crimes are limited to a very few occasions like accidents.  
* If a Platoon Leader gives a Squad Leader an unreasonable order that could wipe out the Squad, the Squad Leader has the right to deny those orders from the Platoon Leader.
